# Engineering OS — Foundation Approved

**Product:** Brain — AI-native commerce OS for DTC brands (India launch; UAE/GCC later).
**Approved by:** Founder (Stakeholder).
**Approved on:** 2026-06-15.
**Canon scope:** Phase 1 as-built (24-week plan, M0–M5, recommend-only AI, deterministic decisioning, single-region India AWS ap-south-1, modular monolith + 4 deployables).

## Ratified framing decisions
- Canon scope = Phase 1 as-built (Phases 2–4 are future Foundation amendments).
- Compliance = DPDP (India) + PDPL (UAE/KSA) as processor; PCI out-of-scope (SAQ-A, tokens only); SOC2 deferred to enterprise phase.
- Stack = managed-first (Redpanda Cloud, managed StarRocks, Grafana Cloud, node-pg-migrate, KafkaJS).
- Auth IdP = self-hosted Authentik on EKS.
- Deploy = ArgoCD + manual gates; canary/progressive delivery deferred to Phase 4.
- Team shape = Advisor-determined (not fixed at Founder+5); minimum viable for the data critical path, scalable toward Scenario C. (Amended 2026-06-15.)
- Principal Architect = Staff/Lead Data Engineer (Data-1), per Engineering Advisor decision — NOT the Founder; Founder remains Stakeholder. CTO retains ADR approval (doc 12 §11). (Amended 2026-06-15.)

